</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[869,1494,762,1107]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,979,762,787]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Taboada-Verona &amp; Botero, 2020" authorityName="Taboada-Verona &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2020" box="[992,1231,762,787]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stizocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruthveronae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[992,1231,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Stizocera ruthveronae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1245,1338,762,787]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Galileo &amp; Martins 2004" authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2004" box="[869,1212,794,819]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stizocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asyka">
<emphasis box="[869,953,794,819]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. asyka</emphasis>
Galileo &amp; Martins 2004
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zajciw 1965" authorityName="Zajciw" authorityYear="1965" box="[1222,1493,794,819]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stizocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroflava">
<emphasis box="[1222,1355,794,819]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. nigroflava</emphasis>
Zajciw 1965
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Guerin-Meneville, 1844)" baseAuthorityName="Guerin-Meneville" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[921,1288,826,851]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stizocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">
<emphasis box="[921,1004,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. tristis</emphasis>
(Guérin-Méneville, 1844)
</taxonomicName>
by the body covered of long and dense setae; integument color and meso and metafemora pedunculate and bispinose. 
<taxonomicName authority="Taboada-Verona &amp; Botero, 2020" authorityName="Taboada-Verona &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2020" box="[869,1105,922,947]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stizocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruthveronae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[869,1105,922,947]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Stizocera ruthveronae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1115,1204,922,947]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, differs by antennomeres III-VIII armed (antennomeres III-V armed in those species, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zajciw" authorityYear="1965" box="[899,1034,986,1011]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stizocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroflava">
<emphasis box="[899,1034,986,1011]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. nigroflava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the antennomere VI can be also armed) and pronotum with four gibbosities poorly elevated. Other characteristics used to differentiate 
<taxonomicName authority="Taboada-Verona &amp; Botero, 2020" authorityName="Taboada-Verona &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2020" box="[1339,1493,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stizocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruthveronae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1339,1493,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. ruthveronae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[869,953,1082,1107]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be observed in the following key.
</paragraph>
